\pard\plain \fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The way I was thinking, I was like, well you know, its hard to tell what a lover wants. Because some wants don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t get said. That would be the easy way, have her just say it, but the thing she wants is something that\u8217\'92s better gotten by not talking about it. She gets it by not talking. Ignoring, even. You have to learn what it is by watching her. Oh, she knows you\u8217\'92re watching her. She\u8217\'92ll brush away your looks and your halfsmirk smiles as easy as if you were never there at all. The way she does it, how she simultaneously accepts and rejects your love, it builds this presence up between you. The world narrows. It\u8217\'92s just you and her. That\u8217\'92s what she wants. She wants to world to disappear and have only two people in it. The way she\u8217\'92s playing... She knows it. You know it. Then you act up and say hello and you come to find that you\u8217\'92re living in your own little world and she really wasn\u8217\'92t thinking about you at all. She was fiddling with her thimble the whole time and that was it. It wasn\u8217\'92t you and her and nothing else. It was her and the damned textile, with you mouth-breathing in background like a horned up jackrabbit. }
