\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  So quick was the Ayramun\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s retreat from the stormy ravine, and so dark was the Underworld, that no one but the lizard brothers had gotten a look at the mage, till now. A hairless, scrawny mage - not fat and bloated like all the others. Blue blood, too. Unnatural form. Strange tattoos running up and down his body. The paleness was also a novelty. A few Ayramun were from the northern continent, born with skin as white snow, but with all the kell-oil they\u8217\'92d slathered on over the years, their skin was now as red as a native Jandrian\u8217\'92s. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I didn\u8217\'92t see it either because this one is so small. Looks barely strong enough to stand up. I\u8217\'92ve only ever seen them as giants. Taller than Ayram. But they can change form can\u8217\'92t they?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Who can?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Who? Put it together girl.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Ayramun\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s camp was set in a massive pit-cave with sandstone walls that ran straight down into the earth. The whole thing was deep and wide enough to rival the Emperor\u8217\'92s throne room, but despite the cave\u8217\'92s immense size it was comfortable, even cozy, because the massive red walls made the space seem tighter, they made everyone feel near, made everyone feel safe. In that pit they were concealed from prying eyes on the surface, and unlike their other hideaway caves, the roof was open so it never got too stuffy. They were able to enjoy the sky without any of the exposure, or danger, of being out on the surface. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 What made the cave so safe was that it had two ways in and out. There was the obvious route of  climbing in or out from the surface, and then down on the sandy floor there was, cut into the northern corner of the pit, a tunnel that disappeared into the earth. This tunnel had a gentle downward slope, but after while the gradient ran steep, so you had to scramble, and then after a little while more there was short drop and it emptied out into the labyrinth of the Underworld. From there, if you could find the way, you could go anywhere.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You could go anywhere, steal a thing or two, and come back without risking a single hair above ground. If you could find the way, there was almost no risk, because even if rich men and their guards gave chase, they would never follow you into the bowels of the earth. They knew they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d never come back.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  If you could find the way, the wealth of the world would be at your fingertips. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When things went well, the Ayramun would bring treasures back to their pit. They\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d filch gold ore from eastern mining towns. Bags of dried pork from stalls in Jeket. They stole wine, grain, and bolts of silk right out of the storehouses in Palace of Eez. They\u8217\'92d bring back pruned fruit and silver coin, stories and laughter, and every now and then a new recruit. But when things went poorly, like when they stumbled back from their ambush in the Junei Pass, the only thing which weighed them down was the awkward weight of the casualties of battle.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Though twenty one Ayramun were killed by the awesome power of Elrahet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s storm, they only brought back four bodies. Two were dead, two were unconscious. Most of the dead were too black and brittle to be brought back to their cave. Only the two had enough left to be useful in ritual: Colm and Papillion.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Of the two living, one of them was found at the bottom of the ravine, right in the middle of the ten-foot deep crater that marked the center of the blast. It was the imperial mage. The entire wagon train had gone up in smoke, except for him. Miraculously he had only been knocked unconscious. There wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t any wound, and he was found there naked at the bottom of that muddy crater, looking like he\u8217\'92d fallen from the heavens. It was supposed that his magicks had protected him. After he was pulled out, not much attention was paid to him because the last and most important body the Ayramun brought home was Ayram\u8217\'92s. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He had only been a little further up the ravine, behind Colm and Papillion, but he fared far better. He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d been blown backwards and had knocked his head against a rock. There was crack on the top of his skull. When the Ayramun found him, pale and limp with his eyes shut, they panicked. Sob had thought him dead and nearly burst Ayram\u8217\'92s belly to save his body from being preyed on by they spirits - but Pella saw that he was still breathing. It was only a scratchy wheeze, but it was steady. He was alive.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Once Pella wrapped his head with a scrap of black cloth that she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d torn from her cloak, she ordered him and others to be carried out of the rain. It took four men to shoulder Ayram\u8217\'92s great bulk into the damp, dark of the Underworld, and it took everyone to see him through, all the way back to their pit cave. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It was the middle of the night the Ayramun returned to their abode. There was no rain, no clouds. Only the moon, stars, and gentle wind. The dead were placed together under a tarred canvas. Needle branches were placed on top to quash the smell. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Ayram, they lay carefully down on a haybed. He was breathing a little better but he hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t yet woken up. Once a fire a was made, and once Pella had seen to him, she ambled over to a dark corner of the pit where the lizard brothers had dumped the mage. }
